<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Qien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I want to start a warrior.  Currently I play a halfling druid (one of the smallest races), so for a change, I want to play an Ogre.<P>Should I even out agi and dex since the other stats are so high?<P>thanks in advance.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kutulu Valkyriur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Its your choice would you prefer to be evened out or do you want massive agi and be able to dodge a lot, have massive str and be able to beat the piss outta things realy easily. Have massice sta where you have massive HPS and never have to worry about getting tired.<P>------------------<BR>--Kutulu Valkyriur,<BR>     Tier'Dal Warrior and Leader of the Downward Spiral</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">zacc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">If the reason you are choosing to be an ogre is for a change of pace, then go all STR.<P>I mean, if you wanted dex/agi, you would choose a small race. n'est ce pas?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kern the Hunter</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">-There is also this to consider. If you build up your STA to some ungodly amount you will never even have to bother to think about buying STA Jewelry and will have tons of HPs. Why not have the highest HPs in the game? STR DEX & AGI jewelry is extremely easy to get with high numbers on them and desireable for filling out those low spots. Who goes out there with the thought of buying STA jewelry? I know I never will unless it is attached to something else I may need.<P>------------------<BR>On the Cazic Thule Server<BR>*Kernan Fenrirson Barbarian Warrior,21st Rank of the Wolves,Naked LongWalk Hating Weilder of the LangSeax."Sons of Fenrir for Halas! For Halas and Glory!"<BR>*Orkus Barbarian Shaman 16th Vision,Spirit Weilding DEMI-GOD in the making.<BR>*Ahirah Dwarven Paladin 9th Tier "Fear me Evil, for I weild the Rantho Rapier!" <P>-"Never argue with an Idiot. First they drag you down to thier level, then beat you with experience." -Unknown<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">zacc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This is a general comment on stamina:<P>It does two things right?<P>1) it allows you to swing more before getting 'exhausted' 2) It adds to MAX HPs<P>1) might be a consideration at some point but generally isn't. If you run out of stamina 5 seconds later in a  fight, it just isn't that significant. The proper solution here is to have someone cast an invigor-ish spell on you when you go oos.<BR>2) the thing with HPs... is that you start witha your max and you more or less lose any bonus you got from your extra stamina in a round or two of fighting. Then its gone. Whereas if you put those points into STR, you will be doing +max damage on every hit, throughout the fight.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hivemind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Plus the extra strength gives you a lot more carrying capacity which is a change of pace too.<P>High STR is fun in my opinion too and the original poster doesn't seem to be asking what's the best exactly.  You might want to get your AGI to 120 and your DEX to 100 and then put everything else in to STR (not sure if that is possible with the Ogre starting stats).<P>It's fun being big.  I like to tower over people and I think a full group of Ogres or Trolls looks impressive as hell.  (of course I haven't been in or even seen such a group in a really long time).<P>Be aware that you will be cut of from most cities because of faction and _a lot_ of zones are very dangerous because of evil hating NPCs, also some pretty important places are inaccesible because of your size.<P>Hivemind (aka Grak, Troll Warrior, Big and Stupid, and proud of it)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Qien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thanks for the replys.  I guess where I'm confused is the dex/agi issue.  I've seen it posted that anything above 75 is a waste, so I'm inclined to get those stats there, and put the rest into STR.<P>I've seen people post questions on stats on everquest.com, but I haven't seen an official answer.  On my druid, it's pretty straight forward - wis=mana.<P>Thanks again</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
